Metadata: Careers in Science (Mud, Carbon and Earthquakes in Salt Marshes): Erin Peck (Webinar December 16, 2020)
This Growing Engineers and Marine Scientists webinar was recorded in Corvallis, Oregon on December 16, 2020
Oregon Sea Grant and on YouTube January 11, 2021

This webinar is for students who want to explore careers in marine science. It features Erin Peck, a doctoral candidate in the College of Earth, Ocean, and Atmospheric Sciences at Oregon State University. Lindsay Carroll, who coordinates Oregon Sea Grant's marine education program, serves as the moderator on this webinar, which was recorded on December 16, 2020.
